{'Product Name' : 'Intel Core i5-11400F', 'Price' : '125.95', 'Power Consumption' : '65', 'text': 'Wanted to upgrade my old 6-year old build. Salvaged most parts and put in this Core i5-11400F processor, reasonably priced at <$200.Everything works/booted fine, no issues  - you will need your own graphics card (salvaged mine) for better resolution and a fan cooler (again salvaged); intel coolers are not the best.  All in all a good processor for office work (not for gaming - get an Core i7 for that).Read more', 'rating': '5.0 out of 5 stars', 'date': 'Reviewed in Singapore on June 21, 2023'},
{'Product Name' : 'Intel i5-13400F Desktop Processor', 'Price' : '165.40', 'Power Consmuption' : '65','text': "I'm working on upgrading my current build and this was just the thing I needed. So many games run so smoothly with this and it's hard to beat. It hasn't thermal throttled, and I'm sure that's because the stock cooler does the job just fine. It works perfect with a 650 watt 80+ bronze PSU. Do recommend for any mid to high range builds.Read more", 'rating': '5.0 out of 5 stars', 'date': 'Reviewed in the United States on April 23, 2024'},
